Performing statistics using both DESEQ2 and EDGER for methylation peaks

medb <- dba(sampleSheet=dbme)
## tet2.Rep1  tet2-/-   1 narrow
## tet2.Rep2  tet2-/-   2 narrow
## tet2.Rep3  tet2-/-   3 narrow
## casper.Rep1  tet2wt/wt   1 narrow
## casper.Rep2  tet2wt/wt   2 narrow
## casper.Rep3  tet2wt/wt   3 narrow
medb <- dba.count(medb, bUseSummarizeOverlaps=FALSE)
medb <- dba.contrast(medb, categories=DBA_FACTOR, minMembers = 2)
medb <- dba.analyze(medb, method=DBA_ALL_METHODS)

res_deseq <- dba.report(medb, method=DBA_DESEQ2, contrast = 1, th=1)
dba.plotVolcano(medb, method=DBA_DESEQ2, contrast = 1, th=0.01)

dba.plotHeatmap(medb, contrast=1, correlations=FALSE)

Step wise guidelines to use RSAT for the TF binding analysis 1. Go to the RSAT(Medina-Rivera et al. 2015; M. Thomas-Chollier et al. 2012) website http://teaching.rsat.eu/. 2. Select NGS - ChIP-seq on the left site and choose the peak-motifs tool. 3. Upload the peak sequence and control sequence from the above extraction 4. Under motif discovery paramters select only Discover over-represented words. Compare discovered motifs with databases (e.g. against Jaspar) or custom reference motifs 5. Under output select display and click GO. 6. After the calculation is finished (this might take some minutes) click on Small summary to see predicted motifs and associated TFs.
